	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 3:25 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Mages are based around 3 essential weapons, two of which are unresistable.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their summoned pets, their damage shields, and there direct damamge/bolt spells.  This is why we mages are the most powerfull class in norrath, there is no comparison.  Wizards? No way in hell.  Monks, roques?  Forget it.  In most cases our nuking abliities will bring is to about 75% of the ability of a wizard.  Add pet damage... a lvl 51 earth pet will quad for 56 and bash for 25, thats half of what our DD will do at lvl 52.  So... are pets pretty much rule.  People talk about this pet recast crap and all that... I have yet to find a time where we need to do such a thing.  In groups its simple, we send our pet in, stand up to nuke, sit down again, rinse and repeat.  Something you will pick up over time is which pet to use and when to nuke.  But its nothing complicated.  One reason why is sorta sucks to play a mage... theres 4 other classes with can take your place in a group( htough you do it the best ).. wizards, necros, roques, druids are all nuking/damage classes.  So.. make sure you make alot of friedns at higher levels.  Um, thats about it, we solo pretty well too, just send in earth pet, damage sheld him, nuke it till its dead.  :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
