	   <tr><td colspan=2>well i must agree that mages are the best damage dealing class i have to disagree that we are the "best" class. we are better then the wizard at dealing damage, but they can make more money easier then we can and will therefore probly have much better equipment at mid levels (29).<br>In my opinion enchanters are better then mages. with clarity they reduce downtime, they can take out 3 white/yellow mobs at the same time, they make the most money with jewelcraft, they are AWESOME in a group, and can solo pretty well. also think about this situation: you are walking along in SK and three harriers start hitting you. mages: they die<br>enchanters: area effect stun, area effect mez, charm one, beat another, keep the third mezed...<br>enchanters can take care of pretty much every situation.<br>mages are great soloers and will almost NEVER be KS from. in a group we are nice to have for the damage we can do and we add another tank. Necros are welcome in a group too but everything they can add to a group somebody ese can pretty much do.<br>the pet recast strategy lets you solo things they other classes could NEVER do. this strategy lets a 34 mage solo a HG. can a druid kite one? maybe if they had clarity 2. can a necro? never get fear to stick enough to kill it. mages use their "two unresistable sources of damage" and can kill things or much higher level.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Speel Lavamaster<br>magician , monk , and warrior extrodinaire.<br></td></tr>
