	   <tr><td colspan=2>Id just have to say, i have a 39 magician, and my friend (IRL) has a 47 enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;I seem to like my mage better.  Enchanters have their good points and mages have theirs.  Enchanters excell in multi-mob fighting.  But they really stink in soloing a single mob.  an enchanter can rock a 5 spectre spawn easy, but most of the time, they are camped by 3 other groups, so you have to solo 1 at a time.  Enchanters also can survive if they need to run, with color flux, mez and so on, although ench most times dont have gate memed, because they have too many spells.  <br>Now for mage, They can solo single things with ease, it takes them like 1/3 mana and its much safer.  Ench pets suck bad, so they mostly use charm.  And if charm wears off, bam.  Magician can also clean out a low lvl dungeon EASY if you wanna farm items.  Magicians also most of the time have gate memed, so its an easy escape spell.  I still prefer magician, because most of the time, you are fighting a single mob, instead of multi.  Especially if you are soloing.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
