	   <tr><td colspan=2>Comparing enchanters to mages is kind of pointless.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's like comparing a cleric to a wizard.  They serve totally different purposes.  Enchanters are great group players with their crowd control abilities and their buff/debuff abilities.  They have some DD spells, but they shouldn't be relied on to nuke if you don't have to.  <br><br>I played an enchanter to 21 and a magician to 27 (so far) and whoever said an enchanter can solo pretty easily must have never played one.  The enchanter can solo, but it's a risky proposition.  Yes, they can stun, mez, or crowd control in some way, but that does little towards taking the creature down, and with all the mana it takes to do those spells, not much is left for DD.  The worst part for me was the constant resist messages I was seeing.  It was quite frustrating.  The thing that topped it off for me was running to retrieve my corpse in SK from the aviak village, getting jumped by a lion while memorizing spells and having it resist all my level 20 enchanter spells.  That truely sucked.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
